<HEADLINE> Sweden, U.S. Pledge Aid to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Sweden and the United
States of America Friday pledged to give a total of 2.25 million
U.S. Dollars to help remove obsolete pesticides accumulated in
different parts of Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
At a donor meeting convened here to seek solutions to the
problem of obsolete pesticides, the Swedish International
Development Agency (SIDA) pledged 1.25 million U.S. Dollars while
the United States Agency for International Development (USAID)
agreed to donate one million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is asking donors to grant it a sum of 4.5 million
Dollars needed to incinerate the obsolete pesticides.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,152 tons of obsolete pesticides have accumulated at
some 256 minor and major sites, and over 100 tons of contaminated
equipment were identified in different parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the representative of the Netherlands also
expressed his government's readiness to support the initiative.
</P>
<P>
The World Crop Protection Federation said it will donate one
Dollar for one kilogram of unwanted pesticide produced by member
states of the federation.
</P>
<P>
It was said that about 250,000 kilograms of obsolete
pesticides have so far been identified as produced by member
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
