<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egyptian Industry Minister Leaves for UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Minister of Industry and
Mineral Resources Suleiman Reda left here Friday for Abu Dhabi on
a visit to the United Arab Emirates (UAE).
</P>
<P>
Before departure, Reda said that during his visit to UAE, he
would hold talks with UAE Minister of Finance and Industry Sheikh
Hamdan Bin Rashid al-Maktoum on the feasibility of stepping up
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's Middle East News Agency quoted him as saying that he
would meet with UAE businessmen to discuss ways of promoting
bilateral trade, investments and the establishment of joint
ventures.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian official said that he would also take part in the
opening due Saturday of an exhibition of Egyptian products in Abu
Dhabi.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 Egyptian firms and companies are expected to
display their products in the exhibition, which Reda hoped will
help market Egyptian goods in the UAE.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and UAE are close to signing a free trade agreement in
the coming months, Egyptian officials have said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
