<HEADLINE> Global Investors Confirm UK as Europe's Entry Point </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 4 (Xinhua) - Britain retains a clear lead in
Europe as first choice for future foreign investment, in spite of
it staying out of the euro.
</P>
<P>
A survey of 150 of the world's top 1,000 companies by AT
Kearney, the US management consultancy, found that Britain was the
fourth most likely destination by global investors.
</P>
<P>
Investors questioned about their future worldwide intentions
rated the UK behind only the US, China and Brazil, and second only
to the US among financial service firms.
</P>
<P>
The world's largest companies cite market size, political
stability, GDP growth, regulatory environment, and profit
repatriation as the five most important factors to consider when
making direct investments.
</P>
<P>
It is believed here that Britain's advantages relate to all of
these factors including its strong commitment to the European
Union, although it stays out of the euro at moment.
</P>
<P>
The survey results suggest the UK's decision to wait for the
right economic conditions before recommending adoption of the
single European currency to the British electorate will not affect
investors' interests in Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
