<HEADLINE> Russia, U.N. Official Talk on Iraqi Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Russia says its task is to
prevent a new crisis around Iraq, Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov said Friday.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting here with head of the UNSCOM Richard Butler,
Ivanov said the task of Russia is to prevent a new crisis around
Iraq, continue the constructive solution of remaining problems and
ease tension in the Gulf zone.
</P>
<P>
He noted that there is a general understanding of the fact that
a considerable part of the U.N. commission's work is complete.
</P>
<P>
It is now essential to clarify issues that remain open in order
to be able to make a comprehensive review of all aspects of
destruction of mass annihilation weapons in Iraq, Ivanov added.
</P>
<P>
He said that such a review would make it possible to lift the
oil embargo on Iraq as stipulated by relevant resolutions of the
U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
According to the Russian foreign minister, Iraq's nuclear,
chemical, and missile dossiers are the "most advanced."
</P>
<P>
Ivanov said that a detailed exchange of views on the situation
in Iraq will be discussed with Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq
Aziz after his arrival in Moscow Sunday. 
</P>
