<HEADLINE> Khatami Sends Letter to Saudi Crown Prince on Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabian Crown Prince
Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz received on Saturday a message from
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami on bilateral ties and matters
of mutual concern, the Saudi Press Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Iranian ambassador in Riyadh Mohammad Riza Nouri, who delivered
the letter, said Khatami wished to discuss with Prince Abdullah
means of developing bilateral ties in various fields.
</P>
<P>
This is the second letter Khatami sent to the Saudi Crown
Prince in less than one month. On November 7, Iranian Foreign
Minister Kamal Kharrazi conveyed a letter from Khatami to Abdullah
which dealt with similar issues.
</P>
<P>
In that letter, Khatami reportedly expressed Tehran's readiness
to cooperate with Saudi Arabia on the flagging oil prices.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Saudi Arabia, once in mistrust to each other for
almost two decades, began to improve their ties since Iranian
President Khatami, a political moderate, took office last year.
</P>
<P>
The two countries saw a big boost in bilateral ties since
last February when Iran's former president Ali Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani paid a 14-day official visit to Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
Hence, the two sides have exchanged a number of other
high-level visits, during which talks on ways of boosting
bilateral ties and shoring up the sagging oil prices were held.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Foreign Minister Prince Saud Al-Faisal signed with his
Iranian counterpart Mohammad Kharrazi, during his trip to Tehran
last May, a memorandum of understanding over future cooperation
in all fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
