<HEADLINE> Arafat Cancels Visit to Norway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser
Arafat canceled his visit to Norway due to the tense situation in
the West Bank and East Jerusalem, press reports said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson for the Norwegian Foreign Ministry, Johan
Vibe, said Thursday night that an aide to Arafat notified Norway
of the change.
</P>
<P>
The aide told the Norwegian Foreign Ministry that because of
the tense situation in the West Bank and Jerusalem, Arafat had to
cancel his scheduled 48-hour visit to Norway.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will return home immediately after he ended his two-day
trip to Sweden, where he arrived Saturday afternoon, the spokesman
said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat flew here to celebrate the 10th anniversary of his
statement in Stockholm which recognized Israel's right to exist.
</P>
<P>
