<HEADLINE> Chinese Ban on Use of Ultrasound To Learn Sex of Foetus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- China's Shandong province has a
new regulation that prohibits the use of ultrasound tests to learn
the sex of a foetus to stop parents from choosing abortion in
their attempt to have a son.
</P>
<P>
In some parts of the province, especially in remote rural
areas, people still have the traditional view that a son is needed
to help one in one's old age and they often choose abortion when
they discover that the woman is pregnant with a female child.
</P>
<P>
The regulation says that any unit or individual who breaks the
law will be fined from 500 yuan to 2,000 yuan and that those who
secretly go ahead with an abortion that causes the mother's death
or disabilities will be subject to further prosecution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
