<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 12 Killed in Car Collision in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Twelve people and dozens
of cattle were killed Saturday in a head-on collision between a
cattle truck and another vehicle in South Africa's KwaZulu-Natal
province, South African Press Association reported.
</P>
<P>
Three other people were injured in the accident near Bulwer,
some 130 kilometers west of Durban. One of the injured was in a
serious condition.
</P>
<P>
The vehicles plunged down a 40-meter embankment, landing
partially immersed in a river. 
</P>
</TEXT>
