<DOCNO> XIE19981205.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> G77 Conference Ends With Bali Declaration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A Group of 77 high-level
conference ended in Denpasar, capital of Indonesia's Bali
province, on Saturday with the adoption of a "Bali Declaration"
and a "Bali Plan of Action".
</P>
<P>
The Bali Declaration consists of 17 paragraphs carrying the
member countries' stand on and commitment to efforts to intensify
South-South cooperation by enhancing cooperation within and among
regional and sub-regional economic groupings, the Indonesian
Foreign Ministry's Director General of the Foreign Economic
Relations Soemadi Brotodiningrat said.
</P>
<P>
Soemadi told a press conference at the end of the four-day
conference that one of the main elements in the document was the
member countries' commitment to carrying out a number of priority
activities to intensify cooperation within and among regional and
sub-regional groupings.
</P>
<P>
The priority activities include the promotion of network
support, institutions and human resources and the empowerment of
cooperation in the trade, industrial and financial fields to
strengthen inter-regional trade and investment, he was quoted by
Antara News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said the Bali Declaration also carries member countries'
commitment to encouraging the participation of the private sector
and civil society in enhancing South-South cooperation through
regional and sub-regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It also carries member countries' commitment to boosting the
involvement and support of the international community, United
Nations bodies, international financial institutes and other
organizations to cement South-South cooperation through regional
and sub-regional cooperation, he added.
</P>
<P>
On the Bali Plan of Action, Soemadi said it was a further
specification of the Bali Declaration and contained guidelines for
member countries and regional and sub-regional organizations on
the implementation of the priority activities.
</P>
<P>
Among the priority activities were developing institutional
support and human resources, forging cooperation in the fields of
transportation and communication as well as revitalization of
cooperation in trade, industry and finance, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, attended by 22 regional and sub-regional
economic organizations, a panel discussion on exchanging
experience on the benefit obtained and practiced in organizing
cooperation among and within cooperation groups was also held.
</P>
<P>
The panel discussion also touched on the role of the United
Nations and other international organizations in supporting the
regional and sub-regional economic organizations in developing
countries and the role of the private sector and business world in
organizing South-South cooperation.
</P>
<P>
It was hoped that the conference's Bali Declaration and Bali
Action Plan could serve as inputs and recommendations to the
South-South Summit scheduled to be held in Havana, Cuba, in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The Group of 77 was founded on June 15, 1964 after 77 countries
signed a joint declaration in Geneva.
</P>
<P>
The conference was attended by ministers and ranking officials
of 132 countries, representatives of international organizations,
and observers from Canada, Japan and South Korea. A delegation
from China also attended the meeting at the invitation of the
organizers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
