<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Stock Exchange
(KSE) index closed at 1,759.4 Saturday, up 36 points from
Wednesday's finish.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 9.53 million Kuwaiti dinars (31.33 million
U.S. dollars) as 51.08 million shares were traded in 1,466 deals.
</P>
<P>
The upbeat performance in the KSE came after its index dropped
4.8 percent last week to 1,723.4 points, a 27-month low.
</P>
<P>
The bourse rallied after Kuwait's Central Bank Governor Sheikh
Salem Abdul-Aziz Al-Sabah expressed optimism over the future of
the stock market.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Salem said Friday that the KSE has been experiencing a
necessary correction phase that will bring prices down to a
reasonable level.
</P>
<P>
"What is happening in the bourse is a natural development
which represent a correction move that comes after a period of
continuous gains during which value of shares reached inflated
levels," Sheikh Salem said.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the present weak demand in the stock market to "a
temporary psychological factor" as investors are expected to wait
until the index hits the bottom.
</P>
<P>
However, since the Central Bank has not yet take substantial
actions to shore up the weak stock market, market analysts doubt
Saturday's upward performance in the KSE will last. 
</P>
</TEXT>
