<HEADLINE> Chinese Businesses Still Have Hard Time This Year: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A recent study by the State
Council Development and Research Center found that Chinese
businesses are still facing great problems and that profits are
down, according to China Economic Herald.
</P>
<P>
The percentage of bankruptcies and near-bankruptcies has risen
to 22.2 percent from last year's 21 percent, and that of
profitable companies is down to 50.7 percent from last year's 51.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Most of the companies questioned cite decreased domestic demand
and pressures from the Asian financial crisis as the main source
of their problems.
</P>
<P>
Companies that issue shares seem to be less susceptible to the
adverse influences and say that they are doing better this year,
with bankruptcies and near-bankruptcies down to 15.3 percent from
last year's 18.1 percent, and profitable companies up to 67.4
percent from last year's 66 percent.
</P>
<P>
An overwhelming majority of the companies questioned think that
the consumer and real estate markets are overly supplied, and 79.3
percent think that the capital goods market is, and 53.2 percent
say that and rural industrial products markets are. 
</P>
</TEXT>
