<HEADLINE> GCC Foreign Ministers' Meeting Ends in UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Gulf foreign ministers ended
their over one-hour meeting here saturday in preparation for the
19th summit of the six-member Gulf Cooperation Council, due to be
opened here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, chaired by Foreign Minister of the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) Rashid Abdullah al-Nuaimi, completed the
preparatory work of the agenda which will be handed to the GCC
leaders for discussion at the summit.
</P>
<P>
The agenda includes issues related to political, economic,
social and security affairs in the Gulf region, sources close to
the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
