meetings which will allow them to take stock of the recent
developments in the region and formulate a unified stand for the
bloc in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan will
attend the Gulf summit, the first U.N. chief ever to do so.
</P>
<P>
