<HEADLINE> Uzbekistan's Malinina Takes NHK Women's Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Uzbekistan's veteran Tatyana
Malinina beat pre-event favourite Elena Liashenko of Ukraine to
win the women's singles at the NHK Trophy figure skating
competition held in Sapporo, Japan, on Saturday, reports reaching
here.
</P>
<P>
Reports said Malinina performed a series of perfect triple
jumps, a sharp contrast to Liashenko, who lacked vigor due to a
cold.
</P>
<P>
Her high score, including a 5.8 and five 5.7s for technical
merit and two 5.8s and three 5.7s for presentation, lift her to
the top from a pre-event third place.
</P>
<P>
Liashenko was leading after the short programme but tumbled to
the fourth overall. She failed at jumps after succeeding in a
combination of a triple lutz and double toe loop.
</P>
<P>
Irina Slutskaya of Russia took the silver and Japan's rising
star Fumie Suguri finished third, up from fifth place after the
short programme.
</P>
<P>
World champion Elena Berezhnaya and Anton Sikharulidze of
Russia won the pairs event, followed by China's Shen Xue and Zhao
Hongbo.
</P>
<P>
The Russian pair, silver medallists at the Nagano Olympics,
kept the lead in the short programme and free skating. They drew
a 5.9, four 5.8s and two 5.7s for presentation in the free
skating.
</P>
<P>
Shen and Zhao, who scored an upset win at last year's NHK
Trophy to become the second Chinese to get the title,
outperformed American pair Danielle Hartsell and Steve Hartsell
in the free skating.
</P>
<P>
The Hartsell's dropped from the short programme's second to
the fourth overall. Jamie Sale and David Pelletier of Canada was t
hird.
</P>
<P>
In the ice dance, Nagano Olympic bronze medallist duo Marina
Anissina and Gwendal Peizerat of France scored the victory.
</P>
<P>
The Russia's Irina Lobacheva and Llia Averbukhk took silver
while Lithuanian duo Margarita Drobiazko and Povilas Vanagas was
third.  
</P>
</TEXT>
