<HEADLINE> OCA Won't Punish Saudi Arabia for Withdrawal from Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Asian sports ruling body
Olympic Council of Asia (OCA) won't punish Saudi Arabia and
Afghanistan for their withdrawal from the 13th Asian Games, OCA
President Sheikh Ahmad Al-Sabah said here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The president, who spoke at a press conference at the end of
the OCA Executive Board Meeting, said there was no legislation in
the OCA constitution to take punitive measures against these two
countries.
</P>
<P>
"We are very sorry for these withdrawals," the Sheikh said.
"There is no article or by-law in our constitution for us to act
in these cases."
</P>
<P>
Despite the withdrawals, the Bangkok Games will still draw a
record entry of 41 delegations and 9,700 athletes and officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
