<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Accuse Iran of Supplying Mines to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban Militia
have accused Iran of providing anti-personnel mines to the rival
opposition of the Northern Alliance, Bakhtar News Agency reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Senior Taliban official responsible for information and culture
Amir Khan Muttaqi said that 400 Iran-made anti-personnel mines
were recently unearthed and seized in Bangi district of Takhar
province.
</P>
<P>
Muttaqi deplored that Iran is supplying mines to the Afghan
opposition at a time when international community has geared up
campaign for banning the production, use and sale of mines.
</P>
<P>
He asked the U.N. Security Council to help stop such blatant
interference of Iran in the internal affairs of Afghanistan as
these mines are posing a serious threat to innocent Afghan people.
</P>
<P>
He claimed that vast agricultural and residential areas in
northern Afghanistan could not be utilized due to the danger of
the mines.
</P>
<P>
Bakhtar News Agency said in its report that the seizure of
mines in Takhar province is yet another open proof of Iran's
interference in the internal affairs of the war-torn Afghanistan.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
