<HEADLINE> PNC Central Committee to Hold Meeting in Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Palestinian National Council (PNC) is scheduled to hold a meeting
next week in Gaza to discuss the Palestinian charter issue, said
the PNC speaker Salim Za'anoun in Gaza on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is to pave the way for the upcoming visit to Gaza
by the United States President Bill Clinton, during which he will
address the PNC, Za'anoun told the Voice of Palestine.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will reaffirm Palestinian National Authority (PNA)
Chairman Yasser Arafat's letter to Clinton in January which
outlined the cancellation of the anti-Israel provisions from the
Palestinian national charter, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Wye peace accord signed in October in Washington asks for
the reaffirmation of the charter's revision by the PNC. But the
Israel insisted that there must be a vote by over 400 PNC members
on the cancellation.
</P>
<P>
As stipulated by the Wye accord, the Executive Committee of
the Palestinian Liberation Organization ratified the letter in
Ramallah on November 6.
</P>
<P>
Clinton is to start his visit to Israel and the Palestinian
territory from December 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
