<HEADLINE> Exhibition on Chinese Revolutionary Pioneer Opens in Nanchang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, December 5 (Xinhua) -- An international art
exhibition highlighting the life story of Dr. Sun Yat-sen, pioneer
of the Chinese revolution, was unveiled here today.
</P>
<P>
This capital of central China's Jiangxi Province is the 22nd
stop of the touring exhibition, composed of more than 130 oil
paintings, traditional Chinese paintings, watercolors,
and works of Chinese calligraphy.
</P>
<P>
Titled "Sun Yat-sen and Overseas Chinese," the exhibition is
the result of the concerted efforts of 160 artists from China,
France, the United States, Canada, Singapore, Malaysia and
Macao. It has attracted 600,000 visitors over the past three years
while touring many Chinese and overseas cities.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Sun Yat-sen led China's democratic revolution, which
overthrew the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) in 1911.
</P>
<P>
This art exhibit is sponsored by the China Overseas Exchanges
Association and the Yin Fong Art Foundation under the Nan Yuan Yin
Fong Group Co. Ltd. of Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
