<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India to Host Asia-Africa Games in 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- India will stage the inaugural
Asia-Africa Games in 2001, the head of the Olympic Council of Asia
(OCA) announced on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
OCA President Sheikh Ahmad Al-Sabah Fahed said the 13th OCA
Executive Board Meeting today agreed to grant India the right to
host the Asia-Africa Games.
</P>
<P>
The two continents will hold the quadrennial games in turn,
added the president.
</P>
<P>
The Asia-Africa Games have only three sports finalized --
athletics, swimming and soccer. The host continent and country can
each add one sport to the program. For the 2001 Games, Asia has
included shooting while India has picked tennis.
</P>
<P>
According to the competition format, Asia and Africa will send
four athletes apiece, including the top three finishers in the
continental games, to each sport. The other participant
representing the host continent will come from the host country.
</P>
</TEXT>
