<HEADLINE> Shopping Plaza Fire Kills Eight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A fire at a large shopping mall
in the city of Baoji in northwest Shaanxi Province killed at least
eight people and injured 23 others, a local official said this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out at 8:30 p.m. yesterday on the third floor of
the six-story Renmin Shopping Mall, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Eight victims, including one woman, died trying to escape the
blaze. Among them, six were suffocated and two fell to their
deaths.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 firefighters and 31 fire engines took part in
extinguishing the flames just before midnight.
</P>
<P>
The clothing department and the shopping center's entertainment
club on the sixth floor were seriously damaged.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, local public security is
investigating the fire, but total losses are not yet available.
</P>
</TEXT>
