<HEADLINE> Beijing Youth Volunteers Active in Public Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- More than 100,000 young
volunteers gave up their weekend holiday today to offer public
service at transport stations, shopping districts and neighborhoods
in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 students from Beijing and Qinghua universities
provided consultations on law, computers and medicine for
passers-by, and another 3,500 volunteers cleaned up the billboards
at the city's bus stations.
</P>
<P>
Beijing established a volunteer association in December 1993
and now has over 300,000 registered volunteers. 
</P>
