<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Li Jiajun Sets World Record for 500m at World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- China's Li Jiajun surpassed a
world record in the men's 500 meters final at the short track
speed skating World Cup series in Beijing on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Chinese clocked a winning time of 41.81
seconds to edge out Japanese Nishitani Takafumi, who won the
event at the Nagano Winter Olympic Games in February.
</P>
<P>
The previous world record was 41.938 seconds, created by
Italian Nicola Franceschina in March 29, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Li's teammate An Yulong also defeated the Japanese Olympic
champion by one hundredth second, with a time of 42.09 seconds.
Takafumi and his teammate Terao Satoru shared third in 42.10.
</P>
<P>
In women's 500m finals, two Chinese skaters occupied the first
two places with Yang Yang (A) taking the gold medal in 46.02,
followed by Wang Chunlu in 46.05. Choi Min-Kyung of South Korea
got the bronze medal with a time of 46.15.
</P>
<P>
Takafumi kept the lead in the first four laps of the race. But
Li, encouraged by cheers and applauds of the crazy fans, did all
he can to overtake Takafumi in the last lap for the victory.
</P>
<P>
"It's a surprise for me to break the world record. I don't t
hink of that during the final, and I just want to surpass the
Japanese opponent and win the title," Li Jiajun told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Takafumi and Kim Dong-sung of South Korea were Li's main
rivals at the international competitions. "Kim Dong-sung excels
in the long distance events, while Takafumi often plays very well
in the 500 meter finals. And we three are foes on the track," Li
said.
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, Kim was disqualified in day's 500m
quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
Li also won the 1,500m race Friday. If he won or took second
in the 1,000m Saturday while Kim was second or fourth, Li can win
the overall champion of the six-round World Cup series.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident in winning the overall title after today's
victory," Li added.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the next Olympics in Salt Lake Winter Olympics,
Li, the silver medallist of the 1,000m at the Nagano Olympics,
said : "I'll manage to overcome the effects of the injures and
age to get good results in 2002."
</P>
<P>
The Changchun native will participate in the National Winter
Games from next January 10 to 19 in his hometown. When asked
whether in the upcoming Games he can defend all his six golds he
took at the last Games, Li said, "I'm not sure because many
excellent skaters have mushroomed in recent years. It will be not
easy to snatch so many any longer."
</P>
<P>
The three-day Beijing tournament is the last leg of the
six-round World Cup series. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
