<HEADLINE> Modern Technology Comes to China's Securities Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Just over a decade ago,
China's first stock exchange was born at a small counter in a
Shanghai securities company.
</P>
<P>
At that time, there were no computers or electronic bulletins
reporting the latest information. All transactions were handled
the old-fashioned way -- by hand.
</P>
<P>
Today, however, a high-tech electronics fair for stock exchange
activities closed here, indicating that modern technology is now
very much a part of the country's securities exchange.
</P>
<P>
On today's securities market, some 10 million transactions take
place every day, and stock-analysis software and the Internet
enable many shareholders to handle much of their business at home.
</P>
<P>
Economists here note that the widespread use of high-technology
is a result of intensive competition in the securities market and
indicates the development trend of the industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
