<HEADLINE> Chen Yan Wants to Be Athlete of Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- China's ace swimmer Chen Yan
said here on Saturday that she wish to be the Athlete of the 13th
Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old swimming prodigy said: "I wish to take as many
golds as possible, but it's hard for me to win all the four events
I enter."
</P>
<P>
"But I want to achieve much and become The Athlete of the
Games," she said.
</P>
<P>
Chen set a new world record of four minutes and 34.79 seconds
in the women's 400-meter individual medley and grabbed four golds
in China's Eighth National Games in October, 1997. She was also
voted The Athlete of the National Games.
</P>
<P>
She will take part in 400m individual medley, 200m individual
medley, 200m freestyle, 400m freestyle and 4X200 freestyle relay
in the Asian Games to kick off here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old swimmer said: "Everybody expects me to win all
the four golds, or even a fifth in the relay race, but I' m not
sure of that, because I am not in my top form."
</P>
<P>
Chen, who won two golds and a silver in the world championships
in Perth, Australia, in January, said:"My form now is not so good,
so it is impossible for me to break any world record." 
</P>
