<HEADLINE> Powerful Earthquake Hits Afghan Capital of Kabul </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A powerful earthquake and a
series of after-shocks jolted the Afghan capital of Kabul in the
early hours of Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here from Kabul quoted residents as saying the
earthquake, which was followed by several after-shocks, is the
most frightening in years.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damages or casualties. And
the intensity and epicenter of the quake were not known.
</P>
<P>
Afghanistan, a mountainous central Asian country, is highly
prone to earthquakes. It suffered two devastating quakes in
February and July this year, resulting in loss of lives of at
least 8,000 people in the northeastern provinces of Takhar and
Badakhshan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
