<HEADLINE> 3 New Ministers Added to Vajpayee Cabinet of India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Three new ministers were
added to the Vajpayee cabinet here Saturday, the first expansion
since it was established on March 19 this year.
</P>
<P>
The three new faces include Planning Commission Deputy Chairman
Jaswant Singh, Former Governor of India-held Kashmir Jagmohan and
Former Political Adviser to Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee
Pramad Mahajan.
</P>
<P>
The important existing vacancies in the Vajpayee cabinet
include the Ministry of External Affairs, the Ministry of
Communication and the Ministry of Information and Broadcasting.
</P>
<P>
Jaswant Singh, who has been conducting secret strategic
dialogue with the United States since June this year as Prime
Minister's special emissary, is expected to become foreign
minister. 
