<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11 Injured in PAL Flight Turbulence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A Philippine Airline flight from
Singapore ran into severe air turbulence about one hour into its
return flight to Manila Saturday morning, resulting in injuries to
11 passengers.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency reported that Flight PR502 was
cruising at 37,000 feet under clear skies when it encountered the
turbulence.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, an A330-300 commanded by Capt. Alfredo Magbanua
with First Officer Jesus Garcia, suddenly dropped to 36,000 feet
before it could be corrected, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
It said that food was being served when the incident happened
at around 11:15 (03:15 GMT).
</P>
<P>
But it arrived Manila safely at 13:30 (05:30 GMT), the agency
said.
</P>
<P>
Medical teams from the airline, joined by airport medical
personnel were on hand to attend to the passengers, it said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 11 injured, the agency said, Jose Fausto Gonzales from
Toledo, Cebu, was taken by PAL medical personnel to the Cardinal
Santos Medical Center for a suspected fracture in the upper body.
</P>
<P>
The other injured passengers were discharged by the airport
medical team after a thorough check-up, it said.
</P>
<P>
The flight ferried 256 passengers -- 10 in business class and
243 in economy and three infants, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Air Transport Office officials have been called to inspect the
aircraft, according to the agency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
