<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading French newspapers on Saturday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- French President Jacques Chirac launched on Friday a new
political campaign by calling for the "modernity" of democracy and
a renewing of public life. In a speech made in Renne, Bretagne,
Chirac said that the French democracy is experiencing a vulnerable
moment and is incapable of answering all the preoccupations of the
citizens, such as strikes.
</P>
<P>
-- At the French-British summit in Saint-Malo, France and the
United Kingdom gave on Friday a serious kick to accelerate the
construction of a European defense. The two countries said for the
first time in their declaration that the European Union should
have an autonomous capacity of action, relying on credible
military forces.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- In a speech to the regional council of Bretagne, President
Jacques Chirac redefined his project for France in the 21st
century -- a remoulding of the democracy. He also proposed the
guarantee of minimum public service through law in times of strike
like that of the railway workers which greatly disturbed public
transport of France in the past week.
</P>
<P>
-- One year after the French government launched the program of
 creating jobs for the youths, 150,000 jobs have been created and
unemployment rate among youths dropped by 10 percent. 
</P>
