<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pinochet Lawyers Trying to Overturn Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Former Chilean leader Augusto
Pinochet's lawyers are seeking to overturn the ruling against the
general because of bias, The Guardian newspaper reported on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
They are seeking the annulment on the grounds that the wife of
one of the five Law Lords, who ruled out on November 25th that
Pinochet was not immune from prosecution, works for Amnesty
International.
</P>
<P>
Their argument was that Gillian Hoffmann, the wife of Lords
Hoffmann, who cast the deciding vote in the 3-2 ruling that found
Pinochet not immune, is an administrative assistant with the human
rights pressure group in London.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was arrested in London on October 16 on a warrant from
Spain charging him with responsibility in the deaths or
disappearances of over 3,000 people during his 17-year rule ended
in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The 83-year-old retired general is currently living in a luxury
rented mansion outside London. UK Home Secretary Jack Straw will
decide by December 11 whether the extradition process can go
forward.
</P>
<P>
The Guardian, citing Chilean sources, said that submissions
have been sent to the Home Office by Pinochet's lawyer, Kingsley
Knapley.
</P>
<P>
The submissions claimed that Lady Hoffmann's position at
Amnesty International questions the validity of the ruling.
</P>
<P>
They indicated that Lady Hoffmann's relationship with Amnesty
could give the appearance of bias, the Guardian report said.
</P>
<P>
But leading human rights lawyer Geoffrey Robertson said that
any suggestion of bias was "preposterous."
</P>
<P>
"Pinochet's lawyers were given ample opportunity to object to
any of the judges before the hearing," Robertson told The Guardian.
</P>
<P>
On Friday night, The Guardian said, a spokesman for Amnesty
ridiculed Pinochet's lawyers' suggestion by saying: "If the
Pinochet legal team have got to the stage where they are now
pursuing this, they are clearly grasping at straws." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
