<DOCNO> XIE19981205.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unsold Macao Stamps to Be Destroyed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Posts and
Telecommunications Department (MPTD) will soon destroy 2.4 million
sets of stamps because of sluggish sales, the Macao Daily News
reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted MPTD director Carlos Alberto Roldao Lopes as
saying that his department has been paying attention to the
preservation value of stamps and that the demolition is expected
to spur the stamp market.
</P>
<P>
He said the quantity of stamp issuance for this year had been
mapped out at the end of 1997 in accordance with market demand at
that time. However, the economy in the Asian-Pacific region has
been depressive this year and some stamp agents have returned part
of the stamps they ordered.
</P>
<P>
Consequently, the department decided to destroy 200,000 sets
from each of the 12 kinds of stamps for 1998. And the demolition
will be carried out at the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
As scheduled, MPTD has issued 11 kinds of stamps this year and
the last will be distributed to the public next week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
