<HEADLINE> Interest Rate in Macao to Go Down Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Following a fresh interest rate
cut in Hong Kong, the Macao Association of Banks announced that
interest rate in Macao will be tuned down 0.25 percent Next
Monday.
</P>
<P>
In this sense, interest rate in Macao will be lowered to 4.25
percent from the current 4.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The association announced interest rate decreases of 0.25
percent each time on October 19 and November 23 this year.
</P>
<P>
Banking sources in Macao estimate that accumulated interest
rate reduction might reach 1.75 percent by mid-1999, when
financial costs will drop remarkably and the pressures upon
enterprises will be eased to a great extent.
</P>
<P>
Real estate proprietors believe a lower banking rate will first
revitalize the housing market and then boost other sectors of the
local economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
