<HEADLINE> India to Curb Violence-Related TV Programmes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Minister of State for
Information and Broadcasting Abbas Naqvi said Saturday that the
government would prescribe a broadcasting code on television
channels to curb violence-related and misinformative programs.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar on "violence in Media and its Impact on
Children", organized by UNESCO, UNICEF here, the minister said,"
All channels will have to abide by the broadcasting code being
formulated by government looking at all aspects of the country's
culture."
</P>
<P>
"We will try to put a stop to programs which take future
generations away from their roots," he said.
</P>
<P>
Public opinion has expressed great concern over the
violence-ridden programs on TV channels in the country, which have
big impact on the healthy development of young generation.
</P>
</TEXT>
