<HEADLINE> Stable Export Growth in Southern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Despite the financial crisis
in Asia, the city of Dongguan in China's Guangdong Province had
more than 10 billion U.S. dollars worth of exports during the
January-October period this year, a 24 percent rise on a yearly
basis.
</P>
<P>
The growth is much higher than the national average of 1.3
percent, and the 3.5 percent average for the province.
</P>
<P>
Dongguan is China's largest export-oriented manufacturer, with
13,000 enterprises manufacturing and processing goods for export,
worth about 9.7 billion U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
This booming business is a result of an effort to improve the
economy by giving priority to capital- and technology-intensive
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The businesses also focus on high-value-added products and
processing. Machinery and electronics goods now account for more
than half of the exports and more than half the products are
exported to the U.S. and European Union countries.
</P>
<P>
Dongguan now accounts for 6.5 percent of the country's foreign
trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
