<HEADLINE> China's Divers Find Opponents in Themselves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- China's divers to compete in
the approaching Asian Games will find opponents in their teammates
as they are set to make a clean sweep of gold medals, Chinese
diving coach Zhou Jihong said here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Our divers will mainly compete against themselves, and we will
take all the four golds at stake," said Zhou, who brought China
their first olympic diving gold medal at the 1984 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
China will miss star divers Gao Min, Fu Mingxia and Xiong Ni,
all Olympic gold medallists who have come back from retirement.
Zhou said that didn't come to Bangkok Asiad as they havn't resumed
systematic training and turn out in the trials.
</P>
<P>
Though expected to dominate, Chinese divers will face some
challenge from other countries, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
"We still have some opponents, such as Irina Vyguzova of
Kazakstan," Zhou said, "I think she is a threat to us."
</P>
<P>
Zhou said her divers will not risk attempting some new dives of
high difficulty degree in the Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
"If they botch in such important games like this, they will
bear much psychological stress, and it will be rather hard for
them to try some other dives of higher difficulty degree," the
former olympic gold medallist said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
