<HEADLINE> '98 Guangzhou Automotive Expo Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The '98 Guangzhou
International Automotive Expo opened here today at the Exhibition
Hall of the China Export Commodities Fair.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 20 automotive manufacturers from eight countries and
regions, as well as more than 150 domestic enterprises, are
attending the show, including such joint ventures as the
FAW-Volkswagen Automotive Co., Ltd. and the Guangzhou Honda
Automobile Co., Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The event came at a time when China is intensifying efforts to
regulate the automotive market, expected to help prosper the
market, especially in the south. In addition, the display will
also be helpful to reinforce and improve the automotive
maintenance services, sector insiders said.
</P>
<P>
China's automotive industry has witnessed rapid growth since
the reform and opening up drive started in the late 1970s. In
1997, China produced 1.6 million vehicles of various sizes.
</P>
<P>
The expo was jointly organized by China Automotive Industry
International Corp. and some other departments. 
</P>
