<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Kill 10 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Friday killed 10 Tamil rebels in Northern province of the country,
a military spokesman said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops involved in
operation Rivi Bala (Sun Force) observed a group of Tamil rebels
and engaged with artillery fire in Oddusudan Friday evening. The
troops confirmed four rebels were killed and a large number of
others injured due to the artillery fire.
</P>
<P>
In another incident at Marippinkarekulam, the troops conducting
small group operations sniped and killed five terrorists, Dewage
said.
</P>
<P>
During daytime Tamil rebels fired mortars at the troops
consolidating in Oddusudan area. Four soldiers were injured due to
rebel fire, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Around 10:35 a.m. Friday in Jaffna District, government troops
conducted a small group operation and killed one rebel, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
