<HEADLINE> India, Poland to Enhance Tech Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 5 (Xinhua) -- India and Poland have decided
to enhance science and technology cooperation between the two
countries, official sources said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Polish Minister of Science and Technology Jose Mariano
Gago said that his country and India were exploring the
possibility of working jointly in areas like submarine robotics
and acoustics among other areas of scientific and technological
interest.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have also signed an agreement to develop
scientific and technological cooperation on the basis of equality
and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, scientific cooperation between the two
countries would involve exchange of scientific and technological
information and documentation through the linkage of scientific
and academic communication networks of the two countries. Besides,
exchange of scientists, researchers and technical personnel would
be undertaken in joint research projects.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the cooperation is to promote scientific and
technological development as well as economic and social
development. 
</P>
