<HEADLINE> Thirty Delegations Enter Asiad Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Thirty of the 41 delegations
have already entered the 13th Asian Games Village by December 5,
one day before the opening of Asia's largest sports event of the
century.
</P>
<P>
Nine delegations had held their flag-raising ceremonies. They
are Japan, Chinese Taipei, Oman, South Korea, Bhutan, India,
Bahrain, China and Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
According to village officials, some 10 delegations will arrive
at the village in two or three days.
</P>
<P>
The withdrawal of Saudi Arabia and Afghanistan from the games
leaves only 41 participating countries and regions at the games
and that's a regret for Asia's largest sports event, said village
officials. 
</P>
