<HEADLINE> Asiad Organisers Issue Warning to Drug Cheats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- All the athletes considering
taking drugs should think twice, the 13th Asian Games official
warned on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Varin Tansuphasiri, deputy head of the Games Medical and Health
Committee, said that the laboratory which will conduct all the
doping tests during the December 6-20 Asian Games is one of the
most technologically advanced in the history of international
competition.
</P>
<P>
"This is one of the most advanced laboratories and one of the
world's top doping laboratories," said Tansuphasiri after a
meeting of team doctors ahead of Sunday's opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
During the Asiad, the laboratory will taken some 800 random
tests of the 6,700 athletes.
</P>
<P>
Tansuphasiri said with the sophistication of the testing
procedures, the Bangkon Asian Games organisers are confident drug
cheats would be caught.
</P>
<P>
Along with random tests, all female athletes will have to
submit to a gender verification test, said Rueangsak Siriphol, a
member of the Games Organising Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
