<DOCNO> XIE19981205.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dung Beetles to Bring Benefits to Thailand: Experts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The high variety of dung
beetles in Thailand is expected to bring the country big benefits
in the future, The Bangkok Post Saturday quoted researchers as
saying.
</P>
<P>
One hundred and fifty species of dung beetles have been found
in the northeastern region of Thailand by two Thai experts.
</P>
<P>
Seven dung beetle species found in the region are new ones in
the world, said Yupha Harnboonsong, one of the two experts, who
conducted a year of research in 19 provinces of the region.
</P>
<P>
The beetles, feeding on cattle waste as well as other wild
animal excrement such as that of elephants and pheasants, play an
important role in getting rid of waste.
</P>
<P>
Thailand is looking forward to exporting the beetles to New
Zealand, which must import dung beetles from Australia and African
countries to solve its problem of an abundance of livestock
excrement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
