<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Gang Leader Executed (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The in-depth review verified the clarity of all facts in the
case and the collegiate bench decided not to hold a hearing in
accordance with Article 187 of China's Criminal Procedures Law.
</P>
<P>
The Higher People's Court reaffirmed the first instance
verdicts the Guangzhou Intermediate People's Court rendered in the
case involving Cheung and four major accomplices. The Higher
People's Court also rendered the final instance verdict approving
death sentences for the five coconspirators in line with
authorizations from the Supreme People's Court in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The death sentences were carried out shortly after announcement
of the final instance verdict.
</P>
<P>
Cheung and his defense lawyer cited three major issues
supporting the appeal -- the question of jurisdiction in the case,
the affirmation of Cheung's criminal responsibility, and the
defendant's meritorious cooperation during the investigation.
</P>
<P>
However, the collegiate bench ruled that all the reasons for
appeal were groundless.
</P>
<P>
The collegiate bench noted that some defendants in the case
were Hong Kong residents and some reside in the inland, but went
on to explain that a number of crimes, including smuggling arms
and ammunition, illegally buying and selling explosives, and
robbery, were all committed in inland areas. The defendants also
used inland bases to plot, plan and prepare for crimes later
committed in Hong Kong, including kidnaping and gold store
robberies.
</P>
<P>
The collegiate bench verified the jurisdiction of inland courts
in accordance with relevant stipulations in China's Criminal Law
and Criminal Procedures Law.
</P>
</TEXT>
