<HEADLINE> Brazil's Beef Exports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Brazil exported 287,000
tons of beef in the first 10 months of this year and received an
income of 466 million U.S. dollars, representing 26 percent and 33
percent increases respectively over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Friday's Jornal de Comercio, quoting the Beef Exporting
Industries Association of Brazil (ABIEC), attributed Brazil's beef
export boom to the price increases of other beef exporting
countries, like Argentina and Uruguay, which sharpened the
Brazilian product's competitive edge.
</P>
<P>
ABIEC foresaw a noticeable increase in Brazil's beef exports
for the year, although there could be a slight drop in the last
two months.
</P>
<P>
The European Union received 64 percent of Brazil's beef
exports, followed by the United States with 16 percent and the
Middle East with 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The association listed Brazil as one of the world's five top
beef exporters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
