<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches New Operation Against Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 5 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan security forces
launched a fresh operation code named Rivi Bala (Sun Force) on
Wednesday with the objective of linking up three key northern
towns, said a Defense Ministry release issued Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The operation Rivi Bala, aiming to capture Oddusudan and annex
the areas covering Mankulam, Nedunkerni and Oddusudan, started
after the completion of operation Jayasikuru (Sure Victory) which
consisted of three phases involving the capture of Omanthai,
Puliyankulam and Mankulam.
</P>
<P>
The two divisions participating in this offensive captured
Oddusudan and brought an area of 134 square kilometers under their
control, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels fired mortars at the troops, injuring one officer
and three soldiers, said the release, adding that the security
forces expect more Tamil rebel casualties but exact figures were
not immediately available.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 500 civilians crossed over to the controlled
area, the release added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
