<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Central Bank Lowers Short-Term Interest Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PLAGUE, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The Czech central bank announced
Friday a one-percentage-point cut in the two-week commercial loan
interest rate, from 11.5 to 10.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
This is the seventh reduction of this key loan rate within a
year from 15 percent to 10.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
In order to reverse the over-tight money market and decline of
production and exports, the central bank has adopted a series of
measures to ease the money market. As a result, the discount rate
has been reduced to 10 percent and the interbank short-term loan
rate lowered to 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
The State Bank Governor Joset Tosovsky revealed earlier that in
order to stimulate economic growth, the central bank would further
ease the money market and further reduce interest rate at an
appropriate time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
