<HEADLINE> Shenyang Airport Reopens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Taoxian International
Airport in the capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province
reopened at 8 this morning after 25 hours' closure due to heavy
snow.
</P>
<P>
The safe take-off of the 6301 flight from Shenyang to Guangzhou
at 7:55 this morning kicked off the normal operation of the
airport.
</P>
<P>
Airport authorities have decided to add another 9 flights to fly
all stranded passengers.
</P>
<P>
The snow started at around 6:00 Friday morning and led to
cancellation of a flight to Beijing scheduled to depart at
06:50. The airport shut down a short five minutes later. 
</P>
