<HEADLINE> U.S. Girl Gymnast Still Fighting Family </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Police are investigating
the accusations that the father of U.S. Olympic gymnastic
champion Dominuque Moceanu was involved in a pssible
murder-for-hire plot, officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The case has been re-evaluated and it is now considered an
open case," police spokesman Robert Hurst said in Houston.
</P>
<P>
Moceanu, 17, who was a member of the U.S. gymnast winning
team, said police officers informed her that her father had
negotiated to pay a hit man $10,000 to kill her friend and her
coach.
</P>
<P>
The alleged plot is the latest installment in the broken
relationship between the gymnast and her parents, whom she
believes squandered her trust fund earnings in risky investments.
</P>
<P>
A judge declared Moceanu a legal adult in October so she could
begin taking stock of how her earnings were spent.
</P>
<P>
A hearing next Wednesday will determine whether the
restraining orders should be made permanent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
