<HEADLINE> Austrian Wins Women's World Cup Super-Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Christiane Mitterwallner of
Austria upset her rivals to win a women's World Cup super-giant
race Friday in California, the United States.
</P>
<P>
"I was only hoping I could be in the top 20," Mitterwallner,
who was never better than 19th in four years of World Cup racing,
said.
</P>
<P>
"I never thought about winning. I can't believe it," she added.
</P>
<P>
Mittterwallner clocked 1 minute, 15.64 seconds, only 0.05
seconds better than Renate Goetschl of Austria. Goetschl won two
downhills last weekend in Canada.
</P>
<P>
Martina Ertl of Germany finished third, 0.04 seconds in
Goetschl's wake. 
