<HEADLINE> Slovakia's Former Prime Minister Quits Politics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Slovak former prime minister
Vladimir Meciar Friday announced exit from the political arena.
</P>
<P>
Meciar said in a statement that he has no intention to run for
the presidency or to seek any public post.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came two months after Meciar's Movement for
Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), the then ruling party, lost its
parliamentary majority in the general election.
</P>
<P>
In the September election, the second after Slovakia's
independence in 1993, Meciar's HZDS won only 57 seats in the
150-seat parliament, 19 short of a parliamentary majority.
</P>
<P>
Meciar, 56, entered the national political field in 1990. He
served as minister, legislator, and as prime minister for three
times in the past eight years. 
