<DOCNO> XIE19981205.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Price Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The average price of
Venezuelan crude oil closed the week at 8.05 U.S. dollars per
barrel, down by 0.69 dollars from the previous week, the Energy
and Mines Ministry said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The average price for November dropped to the lowest in the
last 12 years at 7.93 dollars per barrel, with the year's average
so far to 10.89 dollars, far from the 15.50 dollars figured out by
the government and from the 16.32 dollars registered in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Official spokesmen attributed the oil market weakness to
oversupply and the enormous inventories kept by main consumers.
</P>
<P>
Oil represents 70 percent of Venezuela's exports and provides
over 50 percent of the revenue for the national budget.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela had foreseen an oil income of 19 billion dollars in
1998, but it finally settled at 12 billion dollars, 7 billion less
than expected.
</P>
<P>
Official sources said that the Venezuelan treasury would lose
some 1.2 billion dollars a year for every one-dollar drop in the
oil price. 
</P>
</TEXT>
