<HEADLINE> Qinghai Highway Tunnel Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- A new highway tunnel some 1,530
meters in length was recently completed in northwest China's
Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
The Dabanshan Tunnel, located on Qinghai-Tibet Plateau at an
elevation of 3,800 meters, is first in Asia and second in the
world in terms of elevation.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the tunnel commenced in 1995 and the project
was completed at a cost of 156 million yuan. The harsh climate and
complicated hydrogeological conditions added to construction
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
The tunnel along National Highway 227 is expected to open to
traffic in July 1999. 
</P>
