<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Digital Handset Sales Surpass Analog Handset Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELESES, December 4 (Xinhua) -- Digital handset sales in
the United States through the first three quarters this year
exceeded analog handset sales, representing a major transition in
this market.
</P>
<P>
According to a report released Friday by the California-based
market analysis firm Dataquest, U.S. digital handset sales totaled
10.1 million units during the period, as against 7.9 million
analog handsets.
</P>
<P>
This market's transition to second-generation digital phones took
place after they were first introduced in the United States six years
ago, Dataquest said.
</P>
<P>
Digital phones use a digital transmission technology, which
converts sound into digital at the handset. Analog phones use the
traditional technology that converts air vibrations into an
analogous electrical frequency.
</P>
<P>
Much of the digital handset market expansion is due to the
growth of the time division multiple access (TDMA) market, a
satellite and cellular phone technology that interleaves multiple
digital signals onto a single high-speed channel.
</P>
<P>
Nokia and Motorola are the two biggest players in the U.S.
digital handset market, according to Dataquest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981205.0216 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Market Exchange Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China
today issued the market exchange rates in RMB yuan against three
major currencies. The middle price of RMB yuan against convertible
currencies is mainly based on the closing price of the preceding
interbank trading.
</P>
<P>
The designated foreign exchange trading banks will decide the
exchange rates in RMB yuan against other convertible currencies
according to the tone of the international exchange market and the
rules of the People's Bank of China.
</P>
