<HEADLINE> China Closing Heavy Polluters in Three Gorges Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, December 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government, after
having shut down more than 150 paper mills and tanneries, has
decided to close about 50 cement plants to protect the environment
of the Three Gorges Reservoir, the world's largest water-control
project.
</P>
<P>
The Three Gorges Project will cause a seasonal rise in water
levels of the Yangtze from Yichang to Chongqing in a 660 kilometer
stretch.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chongqing Environmental Protection Bureau, the
cement plants have caused serious air pollution and water quality
problems in the Yangtze and Wujiang rivers in the reservoir.
</P>
<P>
The move shows the municipal government's determination to
protect the environment of the Three Gorges Project. Since more
than 80 percent of the Reservoir lies within the Chongqing area,
the municipal government will close any enterprises causing
pollution in the area without hesitation, according to an official
at Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
