<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2130GMT, December 4 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's elite Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps
(IRGC) and the Army started joint military maneuvers in the Gulf
and the Gulf of Oman early Friday morning, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The war games, code-named "Vahdat-77" (Unity-77), is being
carried out from the strategically important Strait of Hormuz at
the mouth of the Persian Gulf to the waters close to Chabahar in
the Gulf of Oman. (BC-Iran-Military Maneuvers)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Lebanese Prime Minister-Designate Salim Hoss formed
his cabinet Friday.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet consists of 16 members, only two of whom
worked in the previous government headed by Rafik Hariri. Hoss,
69, a veteran politician, was named prime minister by Lahoud two
days ago. (BC-Lebanon-New Cabinet)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ALGIERS -- Algeria urged Arab radio stations to set up audio
and video mechanisms that keep pace with the world development.
</P>
<P>
Algerian Minister of Communication and Culture Habib Chawki
Hamraoui made the remarks at the opening session of the meeting of
the 19th General Assembly of the Arab Radio Union (ARU), which
started Friday in Algiers. (BC-Algeria-Radio Conference)

