<BODY>
<HEADLINE> General Assembly Adopts Resolution on World Disarmament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 4 (Xinhua) -- The 53rd General
Assembly (GA) session Friday adopted 49 resolutions on the
international disarmament and security, the spokesperson for the
GA president, Jadranka Mihalic, said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson told a press conference that the GA adopted
these resolutions at its plenary.
</P>
<P>
A striking character is that the resolutions attack greater
attention to nuclear disarmament following nuclear tests in South
Asia last May, diplomats here said.
</P>
<P>
The resolutions cover such issues as nuclear disarmament,
nuclear tests, prohibition of the dumping of radioactive wastes,
nuclear weapon-free southern hemisphere and adjacent areas.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the just-adopted resolutions are the
establishment of nuclear-weapon-free zones in South Asia and
Central Asia, the risk of nuclear proliferation in the Middle East
and the prevention of an arms race in outer space.
</P>
<P>
The resolutions also touched upon general and complete
disarmament, small arms anti-personnel landmines.
</P>
<P>
The resolutions were presented to the GA by the First Committee
in charge of disarmament and international security matters.
</P>
</TEXT>
